5. Cumulative and impersonal information
The Operator may make use of the cumulative and impersonal information it has collected in any of the above circumstances. The operator may combine non-personal information it has collected with additional non-personal information collected from other sources. In addition, the operator may share cumulative information with third parties including consultants, advertisers and investors, for the purpose of performing a general business analysis. For example, the operator may report to its consultants about the number of visitors to the app and the most popular songs. Such information does not include any personal information and may be used to develop content and services that will assist the user and to tailor content and advertising.

6. Third parties
