8. Use of information gathering technologies
8.1. The operator may use various technologies to collect information from the user's mobile device and / or computer and about the user's activity in the application.
8.2. The operator may automatically collect information from the user's mobile device or browser when he visits the application. Such information includes cellular Internet, IP address, browser type and browser language, access times, the contents of "cookies" that have not been deleted, which the user's browser has previously received from the operator and the referring application address.
8.3. When a user uses the application, the operator may assign one or more cookies to the mobile device or the user's computer, in order to allow access to the application and to adapt the online experience to the user. By using a cookie, the operator may also automatically collect information about the user's online activity in the application, such as the web pages he visits, the links he clicks on and the searches he makes in the application. Most browsers receive cookies automatically, but usually the user can change their browser settings to refuse cookies. If the user chooses to refuse cookies, he must note that he will not be able to log in or use some of the features offered in the application.
8.4. The operator may make use of standard Internet technology, such as web beacons, analytics and similar technologies, in order to track user use of the application. In addition, the operator may include the above in emails or promotional leaflets, in order to determine whether the messages were opened and whether action was taken in their wake. The information the operator obtains in this way will allow it to customize the services it offers the user. And measure the overall effectiveness of online advertising, its content, programming or other activities.
